description: A stranger is seen lurking around the kindergarten, and Kippei is asked to investigate. When he finds the stranger, he recognizes his Aunt Miyako--Yuzuyu's mom! Kippei confronts Miyako and learns why she left Yuzuyu in the care of Kippei's family. Kippei wants to reunite Yuzuyu with her mother, but is Miyako ready for such a step?
name: Vol. 3

description: Marvel Knights - founded in 1999 - has been a symbol of cutting-edge quality not just for Marvel, but also for the entire industry. Now, on the fifth anniversary of this imprint, Marvel is shooting 100 years from the start date for a special event - Marvel Knights 2099. The five stories contained in this volume are set in a familiar time for longtime Marvel fans, but will turn the future upside down, just as Knights did for classic characters during the past five years. Collecting Marvel Knights 2099: Daredevil #1, Marvel Knights 2099: Black Panther #1, Marvel Knights 2099: Inhumans #1, Marvel Knights 2099: Punisher #1 and Marvel Knights 2099: Mutant #1
name: Marvel Knights 2099

description: Miki Sakashita, a 14-year-old girl who is a distant relative of Yuzuyu, shows up to take Yuzuyu from the Katakura family. When Kippei tries to stop her, Miki pulls out a knife! Miki has run away from home and agrees to stay with the Katakuras, but will Yuzuyu be safe around this violent and angry girl?
name: vol. 4

description: Kippei can't understand why Kokoro is acting distant and refuses his touch. She hasn't told him about Itagaki, a boy who confessed his love and forcibly kissed her even though she refused him. Kokoro is too scared to talk about it, but if she doesn't open up soon the situation could get worse.
name: Vol. 5

description: Yuzuyu has a new classmate, Aya, whose older sister takes care of her just like Kippei takes care of Yuzuyu. Unfortunately, Aya and Yuzu overhear Aya's sister complain to Kippei about having to take care of a small child. Kippei starts spending time with Aya and her sister to help out, but Kippei's girlfriend Kokoro is the one who needs Kippei the most...
name: Vol. 6

description: Kippei finds a photo of Yuzuyu's mother in the wastebasket. When Kippei shows the photo to Yuzuyu, asking her if she threw the picture of her mother away, Yuzuyu doesn't remember. In fact, Yuzuyu doesn't even know who the woman is--she can't remember her mother at all!
name: Vol. 7

description: It's the Sorcerer Supreme against the Emperor of the Undead! Dracula wants Earth to fall under the spell of the Darkhold, but Doctor Strange has joined Blade and the Nightstalkers in a quest to vanquish all vampires! See the origins of vampirism itself unveiled! Guest-starring the Scarlet Witch and Nextwave's Monica! Collects Tomb of Dracula #44 & Doctor Strange #14, 58-62.
name: Doctor Strange vs. Dracula: The Montesi Formula

volume.name: Doctor Strange vs. Dracula: The Montesi Formula

description: Bounty hunters Misty Knight and Colleen Wing star in this sexy action thriller, the latest project from writers Justin Gray and Jimmy Palmiotti - an entertaining mix of gritty action, biting comedy and sharp visuals provided by talented newcomer Khari Evans. When four less-than "super" villains - Whirlwind, 8-Ball, Humbug and Freezer Burn - skip bail and team up to rob the penthouse apartment of a wealthy publisher, they get more than they bargained for. Misty Knight and Colleen Wing are on the case. Unfortunately, so are a host of villains and assassins looking to recover what was stolen. Collects Daughters of the Dragon #1-6.
name: TPB

volume.name: Daughters of the Dragon: Samurai Bullets

description: Fashion Week is always a hectic time for models, and this year is no exception. Between escaped wolves, robbery attempts, and overly friendly police officers, Mary Jane Watson, Patsy Walker, Jill Jerold, Chili Storm, and Millicent (Millie the Model) Collins are testing the limits of their endurance. But when a brilliant young set designer is found murdered with three bullet holes in his back, and Millie proves to be the prime suspect, the models are forced to play detective in order to save one of their own! Collects Models, Inc. #1-4.
name: TPB

description: Doctor Stephen Strange embarks on the most important paranormal investigation of his career, as he sets out to solve an attempted murder - his own! And with his most trusted friend also at death's door, Strange turns to an unexpected corner of the Marvel Universe to recruit a new ally. Writer Brian K. Vaughan (Runaways, Y: The Last Man) and artist Marcos Martin (Captain America, Batgirl: Year One) join forces for an adventure that will take the Sorcerer Supreme from New York City to the deadliest dimensions on the outskirts of reality! Collects Doctor Strange: The Oath #1-5.
name: Doctor Strange: The Oath
Vol. 3
Vol. 4

As the Viltrumite War rages on within the pages of INVINCIBLE, the Guardians of the Globe are the last line of defense on Earth. New York is under siege, and the Guardians are called in. El Chupacabra is brought along on his first mission, but hes hiding a dark secret that could tear the team apart! Featuring a special guest-appearance by The Astounding Wolf-Man!
name: Part 3

description: The "Showcase" format continues with a volume collecting the early adventures of the Teen Titans; BRAVE AND THE BOLD #54, 60, SHOWCASE #59, and TEEN TITANS #1-18. Robin, Wonder Girl, Kid Flash, and Aqualad unite for adventures only a teen team could handle!
name: Volume 1

101 Dalmatians
Lucky's Big Break
Cruella's Very Furry Christmas
name: 101 Dalmatians: Canine Classics
Beauty and the Beast: A Tale of Enchantment
Belle and the Beast: The New Adventures

description: In this exciting volume featuring stories from TEEN TITANS #19-36, BRAVE AND THE BOLD #83 and 94 and WORLD'S FINEST COMICS #205, the Titans meet the mysterious Lilith Clay, The Hawk and The Dove as they encounter mystery and intrigue on college campuses and in city streets. Guest-starring Batman, Superman and the Justice League of America.
name: Volume 2

description: Part of the Comics Greatest World (Dark Horse Heroes) storyline.

Story: "First Contact"

Mecha. Mysterious. All powerful. All that stands between Earth and destruction. More than just another "robot book". The famous Dark Horse quality in full color.
name: First Contact

description: Part of the Comics Greatest World (Dark Horse Heroes) story arc. Takes place in Golden City.
name: Inside the Armor
One Thousand Opas and a Dead Body - Part Five

description: The spotlight's on Batman in this volume featuring Detective Comics #327-342 and Batman #164-174! The Dynamic Duo take on some of their most enduring Rogues Gallery members, including Penguin, the Riddler, and the Outsider in these classic Silver Age stories from the era of famed editor Julius Schwartz!
name: Volume One

description: The queen of the Pirate-Ninja Leprechauns, a fairy god-groupie, and the realm's most dangerous 'pocket monster' join forces to escape the most secure prison ever devised by the minds of elf, dragon, dwarf, troll and man: Super Dungeon. O'Mommah, Lulubell and Platinus launch their escape plan by carefully disguising themselves as wads of dryer lint in order to sneak through the prison's clockwork laundry machinery. But the place isn't called 'Super Dungeon' for nothing! Even the laundry's dryer system is a deadly maze fraught with perilous lint traps and ferocious dust bunnies o' doom!

All the Avengers, pet and human, come to understand their recent conflict is because of innocent dragon children. The dragons needed to gestate deep in the planet, then travel far into space. They are allowed to do so in peace.

For their heroism, the Pet Avengers get a headquarters on the grounds of Avengers Mansion.

New Krypton: Part Four

Witness the stunning conclusion to the first season of the 'New Krypton' saga! Things have spiralled out of control since Superman freed the city of Kandor - but now Zatanna and her coterie of magic-users have arrived to even the odds.
In space, a lone Mecha rider goes toe-to-toe with the enemy. Meanwhile, here on Earth, Hyer is disturbed to find himself "On the inside looking out".
name: On the Inside Looking Out

description:
Brainiac: Parts 3-5

The Man of Steel is in the clutches of a horrifying alien intelligence in this issue of Superman Legends, as Brainiacs plan for mass destruction gathers pace! With the whole issue dedicated to Geoff Johns brilliant story, you can read all the way through to the shocking conclusion!

PREVIOUSLY IN SUPERMAN LEGENDS

Years ago, before the destruction of KRYPTON, KANDOR was visited by BRAINIAC - a horrifying alien intelligence that ABDUCTED the city!

On EARTH, in the present, Superman checked in with his colleagues at the revitalized DAILY PLANET - including returned gossip columnist CAT GRANT - before a rogue 'meteorite' called him to action.

This meteorite was a Brainiac probe. After defeating it, he and SUPERGIRL dissected it in the FORTRESS OF SOLITUDE. Supergirl told him that had NEVER met the true Brainiac before.

Knowing now that there may be HUNDREDS of abducted Kryptonians still in Brainiac's clutches, Superman REVERSE-ENGINEERS the path of the latest probe and sets out a track Brainiac down.

He finds him 'collecting' another world... a world that is DESTRUCTED once the process is complete.

Superman has found Brainiac... and Brainiac has found him...
Jack Pierce and his crew are kidnapped by a mysterious mecha, just as his son Terry and Hyer make a desperate escape from the secret Air Force base. The full color excitement continues!
name: Prisoners

description: The 1960s Batman and Robin adventures continue in this second volume reprinting, in black and white, the original stories created for Batman #175-188 and Detective ComicS #343-358. Witness the first appearances of the behemoth Blockbuster, the pernicious Poison Ivy, the obscure Outsider, and more!
name: Volume Two

description:
For Tomorrow: Part Two

Supermans located the epicentre of the vanishing a place where blood flows like water, a place hes visited before a place he left utterly defenceless. How can he protect them from evil outside forces when mans inhumanity to man may be the biggest danger of all?

All Star Superman: Superman's Forbidden Room

Lois has been invited to the most private rooms of the Forbidden Fortress, but she doesnt like what shes seen. Has she been brought there to be mother to a race of deformed superhuman horrors? Little does she know how close to the truth shes getting

Public Enemies Part Six: Final Countdown

Say hello (and goodbye, if Lex Luthor has his way) to Hiro Okamura, a.k.a. Toyman. Clearly his extraordinary gift of inventiveness doesnt extend to choosing a superhero name but not many 13 year old boys have to worry about saving mankind from a Kryptonite asteroid.

For Tomorrow: Part Four

Its Superman versus Equus in a throwdown battle to the death! The secret of the Vanishing uncovered! Plus: who is Mr. Orr?

Camelot Falls: Cold Comfort

Theres an angry alien in Kazakhstan, and his name is Subjekt 17! Superman is going to have to take him down but what does an Atlantean sorceror have to do with the battle?

Yesterday, Today, Tomorrow

The Justice League is the greatest team of superheroes the world has ever known. Now their past, present and future is laid bare in this revelation-packed lead-in to Justice League Legends #1!

For Tomorrow: Part Five

After his part in causing the Second Vanishing, the Justice League of America has called on Superman. Are his erstwhile allies there to support him in his hour of need or will Batman and Wonder Woman choose to put the Man of Steel on trial?

All Star Superman: The Superman/Olsen War

Superstar reporter Jimmy Olsen takes charge of the mysterious P.R.O.J.E.C.T. organisation for the day, just in time for some mysterious rock to cause big changes in Superman! What can one newspaperman do against a superhero on the rampage?

Camelot Falls: Men & Monsters

Clark Kent is taking a pounding from an extraterrestrial named Subjekt-17, while the mysterious sorceror, Arion of Atlantis, waits for his moment to intervene! Can Superman hold his own against a creature who has known nothing but decades of pain?

The amazing "Brainiac"storyline from ACTION COMICS #866-870 is collected in this spectacular new hardcover! Written by Geoff Johns and featuring art by Gary Frank and Jon Sibal, this is the hard-hitting story that revitalized one of Superman's greatest foes and brought the bottle city of Kandor to Earth, setting the stage for the storyline "New Krypton."
name: TPB/HC

description:
For Tomorrow: Part One

Superman returns from a journey to the stars, only to find his adopted home planet an uncertain place. People are vanishing and where was the Man of Steel when they needed him? Even superpowers cant protect him from guilt, and it may already be too late to save the world

All Star Superman: FASTER

Sometimes, even Superman cant catch a break. Lex Luthors been let out to play, and this time hes been a very bad boy indeed. With a band of mad scientists bent on breeding his replacement, and a lady love whos doing nothing for his self-esteem, our hero's gonna need more than one installment to clear this mess up...

Public Enemies Part Five: State Of Siege

The story so huge it took two comics to tell it continues in the first issue of Superman Legends. "When the fox is in the chicken house you have to kill it, unless you plan on losing more chickens." That was Jonathan Kents advice to his son, but will Superman remember it when his hand is finally closing around Lex Luthors throat?
Over 500 pages of classic Batman adventures, from the pages of DETECTIVE COMICS #359-375, BATMAN #189-192, 194-197, and 199-201!
name: Volume Three

description: Batman tales from the 1960s including battles with The Joker, The Riddler, Catwoman and a league of strange assassins, as first seen in the pages of BATMAN #202-215 and DETECTIVE COMICS #376-390.
name: Volume Four

description:
For Tomorrow: Part Six

After facing off against the Justice League, Superman must call on all his powers to battle a quartet of elementals raised by a mysterious woman, as they bring fire, flood, hurricane and rockslide to the streets and skies of Metropolis!

All Star Superman: The Gospel According to Lex Luthor

When Lex Luthor gets sentenced to the chair after being found guilty of crimes against humanity Clark Kent has the greatest achievement of his Daily Planet career a Death Row interview with the most charming of criminals!

Camelot Falls: Camelot Falls

The time travelling magician Arion of Atlantis reveals a world seven years into the future. Metropolis lies in ruins, with only Lois, Jimmy and Luthor as its human protectors! But is Superman responsible for this cataclysm?
Over 500 pages of supernatural phenomena with tales from the Phantom Stranger and his skeptical counterpart Dr. 13! This volume reprints Showcase #80 and spooky tales from The Phantom Stranger #1-21.
name: Volume One

description:
For Tomorrow: Part Seven

Superman has just faced down a series of Elementals who were threatening Metropolis. Meanwhile, the condition of Father Daniel is worsening and, despite the trinity being reunited, theres bad blood brewing between Superman, Batman and Wonder Woman.

All Star Superman: Funeral in Smallville

Clark is in Smallville to see Ma and Pa and catch up with his old friends from High School, but there's something not quite right about the strangers who have arrived to help Pa with the harvest. Will the visit mark a turning point in the life of Clark Kent?

Camelot Falls: The Last Tomorrow

Arion of Atlantis has travelled forward in time to reveal the results of Supermans never-ending battle. The year is 2014, and Lois, Luthor and Jimmy form the tattered remnants of humanity. But theres a stirring in the Earths crust is Superman back?

For Tomorrow: Part Eight

Just how far is Superman willing to go For Tomorrow? The latest scintillating chapter of Brian Azzarellos epic brings a conflict between two old friends Superman battles Wonder Woman for the fate of the world, as the original Fortress of Solitude crumbles around him!

All Star Superman: Being Bizarro Part 1 of 2

All Star stories are bold, new visions stories that are not bound by the continuity of the DC Universe. In the first part of Being Bizarro, a square planet appears in the skies around Earth and begins to rain strange, misshapen creatures on the cities below!

Superman Confidential: Kryptonite

The first instalment of Superman Confidential, takes us back to Clark Kents early days. We all know that Supermans one physical weakness is Kryptonite, but what happened when he first came into contact with the deadly fragments of his long-dead home world?

Superman Confidential: Kryptonite Book Two

We all know Supermans one physical weakness but what happened when he first came into contact with the deadly rock, kryptonite? As we go back to Supermans early years, the Man of Steel takes on a volcano, and Lois Lane proves why shes the best journalist around!

For Tomorrow: Part Nine

In For Tomorrow millions of people all over the world have mysteriously vanished. In the latest chapter, Superman has used the superpowered orb that caused The Vanishing on himself. Hes closer to discovering the secret, but where is he now? How will he ever get home?

All Star Superman: Being Bizarro Part 2 of 2

All Star stories are conceived outside the narrative of the DC Universe, and allow for bold, new visions of the Man of Steels adventures. In the second part of Being Bizarro, how will Superman survive in Bizarro World as the red sun slowly robs him of his powers?

Superman: Angels

This action-packed issue kicks off with Superman contemplating his role on Earth in Angels could his interference in the world of man really end up destroying humanity?

Superman Confidential: Kryptonite Book Three

The stylish Kryptonite takes us back to Supermans early years, and the Last Son of Krypton still hasnt come into contact with the deadly rock. Superman may not have been in Metropolis for long, but he knows one thing for sure he doesnt trust Lex Luthor at all!

For Tomorrow: Part Ten

A superpowered orb has caused The Vanishing, and millions of people from all over Planet Earth have disappeared to a utopian alternate reality. Reunited with Lois, Superman seeks more answers as the epic For Tomorrow moves towards its shocking conclusion.

For Tomorrow: Part Eleven

In the penultimate part of the epic For Tomorrow, tyrannical warlord Zod is destroying everything in his path but Superman refuses to kneel before him!

Superman Confidential: Kryptonite Book Four

In the fourth part of "Kryptonite", set during the Man of Steels early years in Metropolis, Superman finally comes into contact with the green rock that robs him of all his powers. How can he survive this first confrontation with Krypton? And how is Lex Luthor involved?

All Star Superman: Curse of the Replacement Supermen

Free from normal continuity, Supermans timeless, essential elements come to the fore in the mindblowing All Star stories. The Man of Steel has been gone from the All Star Universe for a few months now, but that doesnt mean he needs to be replaced...does it?

Last Son: Part One

Who is the last survivor of the doomed planet Krypton? Superman, right? Perhaps not prepare to have everything you know turned on its head as Richard Donner (director of Superman) and Geoff johns blow our tiny, human minds!

Kryptonian Criminals and Kryptonite

Learn the secrets of General Zod, Ursa and Non once figures of hope for the future of Krypton but now hardened criminals beyond all redemption! Plus, Supermans nemesis Lex Luthor gives a rundown of his favourite ways to take down the Man of Steel!

Escape From Bizarro World: Part One

Its not easy being Bizarro, a mixed-up, nightmare-like, twisted version of Superman with a partially reversed speech pattern. We take you on an unforgettable journey to Bizarro World in this issue of Superman Legends, so buckle your seatbelts its going to be a weird one!

For Tomorrow: Part Twelve

The universe-shaking thrillride For Tomorrow reaches its unforgettable conclusion in this issue of Superman Legends! The Man of Steel battles the evil Zod and the fate of two worlds hangs in the balance youll be talking about this one for weeks!

Action Comics: Who is Clark Kents Big Brother?

Clark Kent was often lonely growing up and honing his powers in the small Kansas town of Smallville. When a mysterious young boy shows up in this Action Comics story, it seems Clark has finally got the big brother he always wanted but is he willing to pay the price?

Superman Confidential: Kryptonite Book Five

The super-stylish Kryptonite continues, as the Last Son of Krypton suffers his first exposure to the deadly radioactive rock from his home planet. With Clark Kent aiding his recovery (how?), Superman presents some very strange side-effects so why is he so relieved?

Last Son: Part Two

Bizarro bursts into the action in Geoff Johns and Richard Donners 'Last Son'. The arrival of a Kryptonian boy in Metropolis has sparked a media circus time for Lex Luthor to unleash The Man of Steels twisted doppelganger!

Justice: Chapter Eleven of Twelve

Superman Legends takes up a story from its sister comic Justice League Legends, as Superman and the Justice League fight a last ditch battle against Brainiac and his mind-controlled minions. Can the heroes save the world, or are the villains right have they already won?

Escape from Bizarro World: Part Two

The Man of Steels weird rescue mission in Bizarro World continues in this issue of Superman Legends! Jonathan Kent has been kidnapped and taken to a square planet under a blue sun can Superman prevail in this strange and disturbing version of his own world?
name: BIZARRO LEGENDS Justice Continues Here!

description:
Escape from Bizarro World: Part Three

The Man of Steels adventure in Bizarro World continues in this issue of Superman Legends, and things just get weirder and weirder! Yellow Lantern, Bizarro Batman, Bizarro Flash, and the whole Bizarro Justice League assemble which could mean absolutely anything!

Justice: Chapter Twelve

As Brainiac exerts his control over the minds of people all over the world, an epic battle heads towards its devastating endgame in this issue of Superman Legends! The penultimate part of Justice pits Superman against Brainiac and Sinestro against Green Lantern.

Last Son: Part Three

After a space craft carrying a Kryptonian boy crashes on Planet Earth, Clark and Lois decide to take him in and raise him as one of their own. Now Zod, Non and Ursa are running riot on Metropolis but what do these vicious Kryptonian supervillains have to do with the young child?

Camelot Falls: The Weight of the World

At the climax of the first volume of 'Camelot Falls', Arion showed Superman a nightmarish future in which Lois, Jimmy and Luthor form the tattered remnants of humanity. The fate of mankind rests with the Man of Steel in the new issue of Superman Legends what must be done?

Last Son: Part Four

Clark and Lois have taken in a Kryptonian boy who crash-landed on Earth, not knowing that he is the son of the vicious criminal General Zod! Now Zod has the Man of Steel trapped in the Phantom Zone does he stand a ghost of a chance? And where does Lex Luthor come into it?

Justice: Chapter Thirteen

Aquamans undersea nemesis Black Manta enters the fray as part of Brainiacs twisted plan for revenge on Earths heroes. Supermans arch enemy Lex Luthor may hold the key to stopping Brainiacs deadly rampage, but will he want to help? Find out in the thrilling finale to Justice!

Camelot Falls: Countermeasures

The New Gods arrive on the scene in this sensational issue of Superman Legends! Originally the brainchild of comics genius Jack King Kirby, the New Gods are a race of super-powered cosmic adventurers from the planet of New Genesis. Will they protect Metropolis or destroy it trying?

Last Son: Part Five

As we pick up the action in 'Last Son', General Zod and the criminals of the Phantom Zone hold Lois and Clarks adopted son, Chris, in their grasp. The Man of Steel has failed, and now hes gone to his arch nemesis Lex Luthor for aid. Can he and the Superman Revenge Squad stop Zod?

Camelot Falls: The Big Picture

Who are Colonel Perseus Hazard and Squad K? And why are they trying to take down the Man of Steel? Some problems are so great that they need the Earths mightiest heroes to band together to solve them its time for the Justice League to enter the action in 'Camelot Falls'.

New Krypton: Part Three

Geoff Johns' 'New Krypton' continues! The New Kryptonians have abducted all of Superman's enemies - and incarcerated them in the Phantom Zone! Have they gone too far in an effort to protect themselves and Earth? And what can Superman do against a whole city of his own kind?

New Krypton: Part Two

The Man of Steel has freed the abducted city of Kandor and placed it in the Arctic, where it has grown back to its original size - along with 100,000 all-powerful Kryptonians. Superman has brought the leaders of Kandor to meet with the US President in Metropolis - only for Doomsday to fall from space and attack!

Superman and the Legion of Superheroes
Part Six: Sun Rise

The Man of Steel and his childhood friends take the fight in the future against the forces of injustice and species intolerance to the twisted Earth-Man! This 31st Century adventure concludes with a colossal bang in this unmissable issue of Superman Legends!

Superman in Excelsis

As Superman lies dying on the floor at the Daily Planet, the astounding All Star Superman enters its final chapter! The Man of Steel, with his twelve labours newly completed, is overcharged on solar radiation while Lex prepares to make his move. Could this be the end?

The Third Kryptonian Part Two: The Escape

Supermans search for Earths third Kryptonian takes him to a remote farm in Northern California, but the crazed alien Amalak is also on the trail. What is the story of the mystery woman from the Man of Steels home planet, and will she prove to be friend or foe?

The Third Kryptonian Part One: The Hunt

Superman Legends streaks into the stratosphere with a stunning issue of Supermans New Golden Age! An epic begins as The Man of Steel searches for the mysterious Third Kryptonian Chris Kent tangles with Robin in the Batcave, as Superman goes to the Dark Knight for answers!

Superman and the Legion of Superheroes
Part Five: Revenge of the Rejects

Thrown into the 31st Century, Superman finds his childhood friends, the Legion, scattered and on the defensive from the xenophobic Justice League. Now a handful of Legionnaires, the rejects, are attempting to strike back to prevent the destruction of Earth!

All Star Superman: Red Sun Day

Superman has been spending his last months completing twelve incredible feats, each more awe-inspiring than the last. Now, with his cells on the verge of collapse, he is dying. Meanwhile, Lex Luthor has just escaped a death sentence and Solaris, the tyrant sun, has appeared!
The adventures of the Phantom Stranger continue in this volume collecting stories from Phantom Stranger #22-41, Justice League of America #103, House of Secrets #150, Brave and the Bold #8 and #98!
name: Volume Two

description: More than 500 pages of mystery tales from the pages of THE HOUSE OF SECRETS #81-98 (1969-1972)!
name: Volume One

volume.name: Showcase Presents: The House of Secrets

description: Nearly 500 black-and-white pages of HOUSE OF SECRETS horror stories in one value-priced volume collecting issues #99-119. These stories features work by horror master Bernie Wrightson, Michael Kaluta, Alex Nio, Sergio Aragons and many others.
name: Volume Two

volume.name: Showcase Presents: The House of Secrets

description: DC's classic gothic horror/romance from 1971-1974 is collected for the first time in this value-priced collection. This moody, atmospheric volume collects THE SINISTER HOUSE OF SECRET LOVE #1-4 and THE SECRETS OF SINISTER HOUSE #5-18.
name: Volume One

volume.name: Showcase Presents: Secrets of Sinister House

description: Stephen Strange was a man like any other. Proud. Arrogant. Cynical. But that was before a tragic accident robbed him of his surgeon's skill, and sent him on a quest for knowledge that would take him to the remotest regions of the far east. There under the tutelage of the ageless Ancient One, the mysteries of the universe were laid out before him, and he became a man quite unlike any other; Doctor Strange, Master of the Mystic Arts! Collects Marvel Premiere (1972) #9-10 and #12-14, and Doctor Strange (1974 2nd Series) #1-2 and #4-5.
name: Doctor Strange: A Separate Reality

description:
This volume collects SUPERMAN #122-133 and ACTION COMICS #241-257, featuring the birth of the Silver Age Superman mythos, including the first appearances of Supergirl, Brainiac, the Fortess of Solitude and more!

**While out of print, there is an exact same reprint as of 2010 with only a slight difference in the cover**
name: Volume 1

description: Action! Excitement! Explosions! The Highest Anti-Terrorism Effort, or H.A.T.E. (a subsidiary of the Beyond Corporation) put Nextwave together to fight Bizarre Weapons of Mass Destruction. When Nextwave discovers that H.A.T.E. and Beyond are terrorist cells themselves, and that the BWMDs were intended to kill them, they are less than pleased. In fact, they are rather angry. So they make things explode. Lots of things. Starring Monica Rambeau (formerly Captain Marvel and Photon), Aaron Stack (Machine Man), Tabitha Smith (X-Force's Meltdown), monster-hunter Elsa Bloodstone, and the Captain! Guest-starring Fin Fang Foom! Collects Nextwave: Agents of H.A.T.E. #1-6.
name: Nextwave: Agents of HATE: This is What They Want

volume.name: Nextwave: Agents of HATE: This is What They Want

description: What? You haven't been reading Nextwave: Agents of H.A.T.E.? HAVE YOU LOST YOUR MIND? Here's a quick rundown of what you missed: SuperheroesfightingexplosionsexAvengersFinFangFoomgiantflyingsubmarinemonstrositiesformerX-ForcebabeexplosionskickingMachineManpunchinggiantevilcoprobotshotEnglishchicksecretterroristorganizationsEXPLOSIONS! Whew! And that's only the beginning! But don't worry! It's never too late to join the party! First up, the Nextwave Squad faces an army of Mindless Ones!!! description:
Superman and the Legion of Superheroes
Part Four: Chameleons

What could have sent Brainiac over the edge? Could it have something to do with Earths coming destruction? Check out part four of Geoff Johns and Gary Franks story in this issue of Superman Legends the 31st Century has never looked so cool.

Kryptonite: Book Six

The slam-bang conclusion of Kryptonite, by the award-winning combo of Darwyn Cooke and Tim Sale. As Lois Lane and Jimmy Olsen tend to Supermans unconscious body, radiation from exposed Kryptonite is slowly killing The Man of Steel a fact that Lex Luthor is eager to prey on.

All Star Superman: Neverending

Grant Morrison and Frank Quitelys masterful All Star stories make a triumphant return in this issue of Superman Legends. After being exposed to a vast amount of solar radiation, time is running out for Superman but what miraculous wonders can he achieve before he dies?

Superman Confidential: Anti-Life

Witness terror in the streets of Metropolis in this issue of Superman Legends. The war between the New Gods and Apokalips makes its way to Earth, and Superman is caught in the middle! Check out the final part of our thrilling Confidential tale from the Man of Steels early years.

Superman and the Legion of Superheroes
Part Three: Lightning and Shadows

In the future imperfect of the 31st Century and with the Justice League hot on their tail, the Legion of Superheroes and Superman go after the deadly Brainiac. An old friend holds their best hope for peace if they can break him out of prison, that is!

K Chapter 6: Cache

Following on from the previous chapter in issue #24 of Batman Legends, the stunning Superman/Batman team-up story K concludes. As the mission to clean the world of Kryptonite continues, Lana Lang makes a choice that may poison her friendship with the Man of Steel forever!

New Krypton: Part One

Kandor thrives once more in this issue of Superman Legends. The Kryptonian city, now located in the Arctic, has grown back to its original size after Superman defeated Brainiac. However, Jonathan Kent has died after Brainiac's final assualt on the farm - can Superman balance the pain he feels as Clark Kent with the joy he feels as Kal-El?

PREVIOUSLY IN SUPERMAN LEGENDS

Years ago, before the destruction of KRYPTON, KANDOR was visited by BRAINIAC - a horrifying alien intelligence that ABDUCTED the city!

Now, after defeating Brainiac, Superman has FREED the abducted city and placed it in the Arctic wastes, where it has grown back to its original size - along with a HUNDRED THOUSAND KRYPTONIANS - all of whom are developing Supermans powers after exposure to our yellow sun! But it's not all good news for Superman.

As his final act before his capture and defeat, Brainiac deployed a MISSILE to the Kent Farm.

Although no-one was hurt by the initial blast, JONATHAN KENT, Superman's adoptive father, suffered a HEART ATTACK while saving his wife and DIED.

The rumbles of Kandor's eruption and regrowth drowned out MA KENT'S cries for help... Superman was too late, unable to be at his father's side while he breathed his last.

Now Superman seeks to balance the pain he feels as Clark Kent with the joy he feels as Kal-El - no longer the last Kryptonian...

description:
Final Crisis Part 3 of 7

Things heat up for our cosmic players in Know Evil, the third chapter of Final Crisis. Supergirl and a group of teen heroes from Japan, the Super Young Team, get in on the action, while hope springs eternal with the return of The Flash, Barry Allen thought dead in Crisis on Infinite Earths.

Final Crisis: Superman Beyond

As Lois Lane lies in hospital on the brink of death, a female Monitor offers the Man of Steel a lifeline. In return for his wife's health, he must follow the Monitor to the ends of the Multiverse and join Ultraman, Nazi Superman, Captain Marvel and Captain Adam on a quest to save all existence.
name: Final Crisis Part 3 of 7

description:
Final Crisis Part 1 of 7

Final Crisis begins in this issue of Superman Legends, as the familiar universe of the superheroes starts to spiral out of control! Check out the first chapter of Grant Morrisons crossover to end all crossovers a cosmic murder mystery of epic proportions!

The Third Kryptonian Finale: The Stand

Superman has discovered a third Kryptonian living on Earth Karsta Wor-Ul, a survivor of Kryptons space militia, the Stellar Navy. The vengeful Amalak has been hunting Karsta and her shipmates for years and now he has come to Earth to finish his grisly task
name: Final Crisis Part 1 of 7

description:
Final Crisis: Submit

What will the world be like once evil wins and everything has fallen apart? Find out as Black Lightning fights for the survival of the human race in this one-shot tie-in to the Final Crisis saga but what part does the Tattooed Man have to play in the proceedings?

Final Crisis: Part 5 of 7

The Evil Gods' forces release the Anti-Life Equation in the latest part of Grant Morrisons epic Final Crisis, turning nearly half of humanity into mindless slaves of Darkseid. In the ruins of Earth, can the shattered heroes find any traces of hope in the ashes of their civilisation?
name: Final Crisis Part 5 of 7

As their dangerous alliance with The Riddler continues, the Sirens will do anything to learn which mysterious villain is targeting them all for death.

description:
Final Crisis: Part 7 of 7

The epic multiverse crossover 'Final Crisis' reaches its thrilling conclusion in this issue of Superman Legends. In the dark at the end of everything, only the Man of Steel holds the key to the survival of the Earth, humanity, and meta-life as we know it! Witness the end!

Brainiac: Parts 1 and 2

Geoff Johns and Gary Franks epic 'Brainiac' story redefines a classic villain for a new generation. As a palate cleanser from the ultimate crossover, check out the first two parts, First Contact and Hide and Seek, in this action-packed issue of Superman Legends.

PREVIOUSLY IN FINAL CRISIS...

Batman is dead, annihilated by DARKSEID'S OMEGA BEAMS ... but not before mortally wounding Darkseids body, drawing the dread attention of the BLACK RIDER , the incarnation of death. Following hot on the heels of the FLASHES . Death sundered Darkseid's spirit from his body.

All that's left of the universe is fragments of compacted space-time, held together by pure will: the FORTRESS OF SOLITUDE , the WATCHTOWER, the DAILY PLANET ... last outposts of humanity in a multiverse that can no longer support them.

It is here, in the dark at the end of everything, that SUPERMAN is building a WEAPON he glimpsed in the 31ST CENTURY ... a weapon to set everything right. To defeat Darkseid's spirit. To dual with MANDRAKK , fallen Monitor and incarnation of ultimate evil.

Superman's story is powerful. The first of all superheroes, the PRIMAL MYTH , replicated through all the worlds of the multiverse. But will it be enough? Can it prove the most powerful story of all...?
name: Final Crisis Part 7 of 7 - THE INCREDIBLE CONCLUSION!

description:
Camelot Falls: The Fall

Two massive storylines come to their sensational conclusions in this issue of Superman Legends! In the penultimate chapter of the epic 'Camelot Falls', The Man of Steel teams up with his trusted ally and powerful magician Zatanna, and Subjekt 17 decides to get a little punchy.

Last Son: Conclusion

Its all out warfare in Metropolis as General Zod and his army of super-powered Kryptonian criminals make their last attempt to take over the world! Can Superman and Lex Luthors Revenge Squad stop him? Youll be talking about this one for weeks to come!

Camelot Falls: Tide and Torrent

Is Superman willing to risk all of humanity for what he thinks is right? Or will Arion of Atlantis stop the Man of Steel and avert the catastrophe that he sees in our future? Find out all the answers in this issues knock-down, two-fisted finale to Camelot Falls!

Alien World: Part One

The Man of Steel discovers that the 31st Century isnt the fun place he thought it was in this issue of Superman Legends. The Justice League has been visited by the Legion of Superheroes, but these travellers from the future have provided them with more questions than answers.

Superman Confidential: The Edge of Forever

Has Clark Kents presence in Metropolis started to attract a brand new breed of super-villain like Victor Volcanum? In this story from Supermans early years, the Man of Steel becomes acquainted with the New Gods and it isnt long before a fist-fight or two erupts!

K Chapter 2: Known Deposits

Bruce Wayne has reluctantly agreed to help Clark Kent round up all the Kryptonite in the world, but with Aquaman standing in the way, it aint gonna be easy! We pick up Known Deposits following the first chapter published in issue 22 of our sister comic Batman Legends.

Superman Confidential: Supertown

The latest issue of Superman Legends kicks off with a crash course in the history of the New Gods. Kidnapped by Orion, hunted through the wilds of New Genesis, imperiled by Highfather the Man of Steel is set to learn a few harsh lessons about the nature of reality!

Superman and the Legion of Superheroes

Part Two: Illegal Aliens

Superman continues to find out some dark truths about his childhood friends, as the twisted Justice League of Earth makes its debut! The Legion are broken and scattered, leaving Earth a fearful and xenophobic place. What now for the Man of Steel in the 31st Century?

K Part Four: WSDs

Who are The Last Line, and how are they connected to Kryptonite? In their mission to eradicate Kryptonite from Planet Earth, Batman and Superman stumble across the US governments huge stash of the green stuff! K continues from issue #23 of Batman Legends.

In 1985, DC Comics dramatically altered comics' original universe with Crisis on Infinite Earths - an unforgettable, defining event in comics history that streamlined DCU continuity forever. Nine years later, the heroes of the DCU found the temporal fabric of their new reality unraveling, and the biggest threat since the Crisis was about to be revealed.

Zero Hour: Crisis in Time collects this landmark event. Written and pencilled by Dan Jurgens (SUPERMAN: DAY OF DOOM) and inked by Jerry Ordway (JLA/PLANETARY, WONDER WOMAN), Zero Hour chronicles the discovery by DC's greatest heroes of a tidal wave of temporal disruptions, as they band together to combat chronal chaos. A thousand years in the future, other heroes face even greater havoc. Villainy is afoot, as criminal masterminds ten centuries apart try to take advantage of time's shattered visage for their own purposes. But each of them, hero and villain alike, may be nothing more than a pawn in the schemes of the ultimate time villain, whose machinations are on a scale beyond imagining!
name: TPB

description: In this dynamite conclusion, Kratos faces his greatest test to date the behemoth Gyges, the living island! This massive foe stands between Kratos and ultimate success. This tale spins out of the Sony videogame God of War III, which was voted "Most Anticipated Game of 2010" at this year's Spike Awards.

As the new Kato readies herself for her upcoming battle with the Black Hornet, new foes loom on the horizon. After taking out his league of teen ninja assassins, Kato finds herself the target of Takeshi. This issue also introduces a major new character into Kato's world... one that will play a pivotal role in the months to come. Also, the original Kato arrives in the US. Can the two Kato's _ father and daughter - get along well enough to prepare for their showdown with Black Hornet? This issue ties into the Kevin Smith Green Hornet series!
